<paragraph id="8BF5D959FFA53C5FFF6BBA60FDAE815C" blockId="3.[151,1437,1076,1355]" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">
This species was described from the female 
<typeStatus id="54F167FBFFA53C5FFD72BA60FD668059" box="[654,752,1076,1102]" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">holotype</typeStatus>
plus 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA53C5FFCD2BA61FC268059" box="[814,944,1076,1103]" pageId="3" pageNumber="241" type="female">ten females</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA53C5FFC14BA61FBE28059" box="[1000,1140,1076,1103]" pageId="3" pageNumber="241" type="male">seven males</specimenCount>
, taken in the rolled leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA53C5FFF4ABA0CFEE48065" box="[182,370,1112,1138]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dilleniaceae" genus="Hibbertia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dilleniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lucens">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA53C5FFF4ABA0CFEE48065" box="[182,370,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">Hibbertia lucens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA53C5FFE83BA03FD878065" box="[383,529,1111,1138]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dilleniaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dilleniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Dilleniaceae</taxonomicName>
] at Mont Koghi just north of 
<location id="8E958F82FFA53C5FFCA1BA0DFC298064" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E3684FFFA53C5FFF6BBDD1FDAE815C:8E958F82FFA53C5FFCA1BA0DFC298064" box="[861,959,1113,1139]" country="New Caledonia" county="Noumea in April" municipality="Mont Do" name="Noumea" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">Noumea</location>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F35D99C9FFA53C5FFC36BA0DFBED8065" box="[970,1147,1112,1139]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
. The maxillary stylets are exceptionally long, and commonly cross over each other medially in the head (
<figureCitation id="1371C5DCFFA53C5FFBF6BA28FBC58081" box="[1034,1107,1148,1174]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1770,1794]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[153,1434,181,1746]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Heads of paratypes of Teuchothrips species. (1) cleistanthi; (2) kraussi; (3) ornatus; (4) noumeaensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405146/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">Figs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1371C5DCFFA53C5FFBA3BA28FBF98080" box="[1119,1135,1148,1175]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1755]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,237,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-57@4.[151,1435,237,1708]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5–12. Teuchothrips and Neocecidothrips. (5) T. ornatus head (LAM5607). N. pacificus holotype 6–12: (6) head; (7) fore tibia &amp; tarsus; (8) antenna; (9) mesonotum, metanotum &amp; pelta. (10) head &amp; pronotum; (11) pronotum; (12) prosternum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405148/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">5</figureCitation>
). The vertex is extensively reticulate, the postoccipital ridge simple, and the pronotal anteromarginal setae very small with the posteroangular setae elongate. From the type series, 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA53C5FFDC5BA90FD5380C9" box="[569,709,1220,1246]" pageId="3" pageNumber="241" type="female">three female</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA53C5FFD01BA91FCF380C9" box="[765,869,1220,1247]" pageId="3" pageNumber="241" type="male">two male</specimenCount>
<typeStatus id="54F167FBFFA53C5FFC91BA91FC4E80C8" box="[877,984,1221,1247]" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">paratypes</typeStatus>
were studied on loan from the 
<location id="8E958F82FFA53C5FFAC6BA91FE718115" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E3684FFFA53C5FFF6BBDD1FDAE815C:8E958F82FFA53C5FFAC6BA91FE718115" country="New Caledonia" county="Noumea in April" municipality="Mont Do" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">Museum National d’Histoire Naturelle</location>
, Paris. In addition, a series of 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA53C5FFCB7BABCFC728115" box="[843,996,1256,1282]" pageId="3" pageNumber="241" type="female">eight females</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA53C5FFBDCBABCFB108115" box="[1056,1158,1256,1282]" pageId="3" pageNumber="241" type="male">14 males</specimenCount>
more recently collected were studied. 
<location id="8E958F82FFA53C5FFECEBB58FEE38131" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E3684FFFA53C5FFF6BBDD1FDAE815C:8E958F82FFA53C5FFECEBB58FEE38131" box="[306,373,1292,1318]" country="New Caledonia" county="Noumea in April" municipality="Mont Do" name="These" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">These</location>
were taken from the apical buds of an 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA53C5FFCD9BB58FC048131" box="[805,914,1292,1318]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dilleniaceae" genus="Hibbertia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dilleniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA53C5FFCD9BB58FC048131" box="[805,914,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">Hibbertia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species on 
<collectingMunicipality id="6B914323FFA53C5FFBEEBB59FBEC8130" box="[1042,1146,1293,1319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">Mont Do</collectingMunicipality>
, about 
<quantity id="4CB274BCFFA53C5FFB36BB58FA9F8131" box="[1226,1289,1292,1318]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="241" unit="km" value="70.0">70km</quantity>
northwest of 
<collectingCounty id="6294A1D5FFA53C5FFF6BBB65FEC0815D" box="[151,342,1328,1355]" pageId="3" pageNumber="241">Noumea in April</collectingCounty>
, 2012 (LAM 5607).
</paragraph>
